Flooding has also been reported in Bellville South, Goodwood and Belhar. CAPE TOWN - Patients at community day centres in Belhar, Parow and Ravensmead have had to be referred to alternative health care facilities due to flooding. Flooding has also been reported in Bellville South, Goodwood and Belhar. Overnight, strong wind brought down power lines in several other areas. Two law enforcement officials sustained minor injuries when a tree was blown over on Constantia Main Road and landed on their vehicle. Disaster Risk spokesperson Charlotte Powell said: “Due to the severity of the flooding incident, the disaster coordinating team was activated. At this stage, roadways have been cleared and trees have been removed. Electricity has not yet been restored in some areas and technicians are on site.” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)